attributes.Long form description: The student changes the configuration of their controllers and game card, then turns on and off their Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Transcription: Please change the control from handheld mode to Joycon comfort grip.

attributes.Action sentence: The student exchanges the two Joy-Cons from handheld mode into a comfort grip.

attributes.Transcription: So, take the red and blue controllers, and take them off by pressing the button on the back and pulling them up.
There should be a circular black button at the back that you need to press.
And then pull it upwards.
The Joycon comfort grip is the black controller thing in the back so put the red and blue controllers on them.
Nice, well done.
Now, please change the controller from the Joycon comfort grip to two Joycons

attributes.Action sentence: The student changes to a single Joy-Con controller with a strap lock.

attributes.Transcription: Attach those to the black and... To the red and blue controllers.
Make sure to line up the plus and the minuses.
And press the white lock at the bottom.
Just press inwards until clicks.
Nice, well done.
Now, please change the controllers from two Joycons back into hanheld mode.

attributes.Action sentence: The student changes the Joy-Cons back to handheld mode.

attributes.Transcription: Nice, well done.
Now, please stand the Nintendo Switch on the table using the kickstand.

attributes.Action sentence: The student places the Nintendo Switch on the table using the kickstand.

attributes.Transcription: At the bottom, right on the back of the Nintendo Switch.
There should be something on the bottom left. Sorry, there should be something that you can pull out.
Nice, well done.
Now, please change the game card in the Switch.

attributes.Action sentence: The student changes the game card of the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Transcription: The game card is in the top, right of the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student pulls the game card instead of pressing it.

attributes.Transcription: You could just press on it, so it pops out.
Nice, well done.
Now, please change the micro SD card.

attributes.Action sentence: The student exchanges the SD card of the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Transcription: The micro SD card is under the kickstand.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student needs tu push the sd card.

attributes.Transcription: You should be able to just push it in, so that comes out.
You probably have to switch it around.
Nice, well done.
Now, please turn on the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Action sentence: The student turns on the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Transcription: Good Job!
Now, please turn off the Nintendo Switch again.

attributes.Action sentence: The student turns off their Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student accidentally removes the Joy-Con.

attributes.Transcription: It's currently only in standby mode, you have to press the button for three seconds, at least.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student removes accidentally the Joy-Con.

attributes.Transcription: Now, go on to power off central button.
Nice, well done.
You can stop the recording now.
